    <item>
      <title>Data, Collections &amp; Records</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/data/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/data/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;data&#34;&gt;Data&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Or the Excel file which contains all the listings/records which will be served by the directory. File should be of type &lt;code&gt;.xlsx&lt;/code&gt; only.&#xA;All the major spreadsheet software allow exporting to Excel format which saves the file as &lt;code&gt;.xlsx&lt;/code&gt; which can be then imported.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It is possible to host multiple collections per directory. Consider the example of &amp;ldquo;job listings&amp;rdquo; directory. The straightforward collection&#xA;would be collection of &amp;ldquo;jobs&amp;rdquo; but you can also have &amp;ldquo;companies&amp;rdquo;, &amp;ldquo;positions&amp;rdquo; or &amp;ldquo;locations&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Deploying your directory</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/go-live-and-update/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/go-live-and-update/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;go-live&#34;&gt;Go Live&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Its as easy as clicking the &amp;ldquo;Go Live&amp;rdquo; button.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;steps&#34;&gt;Steps&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Create &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/docs/new-directory&#34;&gt;new directory&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;A new card will be visible on dashboard with label &amp;ldquo;New Directory&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/assets/go-live-and-update/directory-card-1.png&#34; alt=&#34;New Directory&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol start=&#34;2&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/docs/studio&#34;&gt;Edit the design&lt;/a&gt; &amp;amp; &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/docs/page-seo&#34;&gt;pSEO&lt;/a&gt; is configured for the pages&#xA;The &amp;ldquo;Go Live&amp;rdquo; button on the card should be enabled now&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/assets/go-live-and-update/directory-card-2.png&#34; alt=&#34;Go Live&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol start=&#34;3&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Click &amp;ldquo;Go Live&amp;rdquo; &amp;amp; wait till server is provisined usually takes a minute or two&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/docs/update-dns&#34;&gt;Update DNS records&lt;/a&gt; with your domain provider&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Kriti Studio</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/studio/studio/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/studio/studio/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Kriti Studio is a web-only, no code, drag and drop builder which&#xA;allow you to design your sites however you see fit. Its your brand after all.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;prerequisites&#34;&gt;Prerequisites&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;A directory is already created. &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/docs/new-directory&#34;&gt;How to?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;All the data is ready in &lt;code&gt;.xlsx&lt;/code&gt; file and imported. &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/docs/data&#34;&gt;How to?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;post-import--web-pages&#34;&gt;Post import &amp;amp; web pages&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;After importing data, some web pages are auto generated based on the data. You can view this pages on top left corner drop down menu.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>New Directory</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/new-directory/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/new-directory/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Starting a new directory? You need 3 things:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;title&lt;/strong&gt;: An internal only directory title to identify it amongst other directories on your dashboard.&#xA;Title should be a single word, alphabets only (no numbers or special characters) and unique amongst other directories on your dashboard.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;domain&lt;/strong&gt;: An URL where you&amp;rsquo;ll host the directory. Once the directory is published, DNS records will be shared&#xA;which customers are expected to add them to thier domain provider so that the directory can be served on that domain/URL.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;data&lt;/strong&gt;: An excel (&amp;quot;.xlsx&amp;quot;) file which contains all the collections &amp;amp; listings. There are certain structure which is expected from&#xA;this excel file. This is explained in the &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/docs/data&#34;&gt;next section&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;As long as Kriti/Directory is in BETA, only 1 directory per user restriction is imposed.&#xA;Please contact &lt;a href=&#34;mailto:vinay.gaykar+kriti-support@proton.me&#34;&gt;support&lt;/a&gt; for help.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Page Metadata &amp; SEO</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/page-seo/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/page-seo/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;This documentation explains how to add page meta data in your application using the built-in &amp;ldquo;Page Meta &amp;amp; SEO&amp;rdquo; panel. The panel provides an easy way to manage meta data fields to improve your pageâ€™s SEO. Follow the instructions below to add new meta data fields and input the necessary information.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;video controls width=&#34;100%&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;source src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/assets/docs/page-seo/seo-demo.webm&#34; type=&#34;video/webm&#34; /&gt;&#xA;&lt;/video&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;adding-metadata&#34;&gt;Adding Metadata&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Accessing the &amp;ldquo;Page Meta &amp;amp; SEO&amp;rdquo; Panel&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Locate and click the accordian &amp;ldquo;Page Meta &amp;amp; SEO&amp;rdquo; on top left corner below page selector. Clicking on it will expand the section to reveal the meta data form.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Setting Up Your DNS Records</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/update-dns/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/update-dns/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;After clicking &amp;ldquo;Go Live&amp;rdquo; on your dashboard, you&amp;rsquo;ll need to point your domain to your new server. Here&amp;rsquo;s how to get your IP address and update your DNS records.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;getting-your-ip-address&#34;&gt;Getting Your IP Address&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Click the &lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;View DNS&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt; button on your directory card&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Copy the IP address shown&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Keep this handy - you&amp;rsquo;ll need it for the next steps&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;updating-dns-records-by-provider&#34;&gt;Updating DNS Records by Provider&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;godaddy&#34;&gt;GoDaddy&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Log into your GoDaddy account&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Go to &lt;strong&gt;My Products&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;gt; &lt;strong&gt;DNS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Find your domain and click &lt;strong&gt;Manage&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Look for the &lt;strong&gt;A Record&lt;/strong&gt; with &amp;ldquo;@&amp;rdquo; or your domain name&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Click the pencil icon to edit&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Replace the old IP with your new IP address&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Click &lt;strong&gt;Save&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Changes take 1-24 hours to work everywhere.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
